description: SHANGHAI - The Middle East saw the most turbulent tensions after Hamas’s attack on October 7, 2023, through the first half of 2024. The rationales behind the growing tensions are numerous, but the primary one should be Benjamin Netanyahu’s crazy unreachable and unreasonable objectives. Judging by Netanyahu’s incalcitrant character, the tensions will continue, and the Middle East should prepare for the worst weather.

description: MADRID - The elections in Iran will have a runoff on July 5th, after none of the candidates reached the necessary majority (50% plus one of the votes) in the elections on June 28th.
